  "explanation": "In determining the appropriate sentence, the court must balance the severity of the crime with the mitigating circumstances surrounding the defendant. Embezzlement is a serious offense that involves a significant breach of trust between an employee and their employer. However, the defendant has no prior criminal record, which indicates this is an isolated lapse in judgment rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already begun making restitution, showing genuine remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. The courtroom disruption by a spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded, as emotions and public outbursts have no place in the objective and fair administration of justice. A 10-year sentence for a first-time, non-violent offense of this magnitude would be absurdly disproportionate. Taking into account the need for accountability and deterrence, while also recognizing the defendant's rehabilitation potential and partial restitution, a short period of incarceration followed by probation and full restitution is the most appropriate course of action.",
